    "notes": "Phase 2 (2026-05-31). Radius: Ligi et al. 2019 VEGA/CHARA interferometry (theta_LD = 1.035 +/- 0.021 mas) gives R = 0.726 +/- 0.014 Rsun, replacing the prior DB unverified 0.778 Rsun (Gillon 2017). Mass tiebreak: Ligi 2019 report a DIRECT mass M = 0.696 +/- 0.078 Msun from the interferometric radius combined with the transit-derived stellar density (rho = 1.82 +/- 0.19 rho_sun); this is recommended over the evolutionary value (Motalebi 2015 SYCLIST 0.78 +/- 0.02; Ligi C2kSMO range 0.755-0.810, reference model 0.755 +/- 0.040) because it is a measurement rather than a model, though it carries ~11% uncertainty and no clean schema method (recorded as method=unverified, the escape hatch for a real technique outside the whitelist). The two agree at ~1.5 sigma. Teff = 4858 +/- 50 K (Ligi interferometric, F_bol + theta_LD); Motalebi SPC gives 4941 +/- 50 K (alt). Luminosity L = 0.264 +/- 0.004 Lsun (Ligi bolometric flux). Activity: Johnson et al. 2016 measure an 11.7 yr (4230 +/- 100 d) S-index magnetic cycle and a mean <log R'HK> = -4.89. Rotation is genuinely contested: Motalebi 2015 found 42.3 d from log R'HK + CCF FWHM/bisector periodograms; Johnson 2016 found 22.83 +/- 0.03 d in the Ca II S_HK series (possibly the first harmonic of ~45 d differential rotation, and identical to planet f's 22.8 d period — the basis for f being contested); Vogt 2015 estimated ~20 d from v sin i = 1.8 km/s. No photometric period exists (Vogt APT photometry is flat to ~0.0002 mag), so all candidates use method=unverified. Recommended: Johnson 22.83 d (most precise, dedicated S_HK analysis), with the 42.3 d alternative documented. Age poorly constrained (models 0.2-13.8 Gyr; activity ~3-9 Gyr) -> omitted. [Fe/H] skipped per policy. Effectively single: a V~9.4 M dwarf lies at ~106.6\" (~700 AU projected, P~20 kyr; Eggleton & Tokovinin 2008 via Vogt 2015) -> meta note only, NOT a binary_orbits entry."
